ght: 0; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-left: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(-4px) translateX(8px);\"></div></div></div></a> <p style=\" margin:8px 0 0 0; padding:0 4px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BoP7ix6DIO3/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" color:#000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none; word-wrap:break-word;\" target=\"_blank\">Our A Team &#8211; all ready for Friday! #saladstop</a></p> <p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\">A post shared by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/saladstopsg/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px;\" target=\"_blank\"> SaladStop!</a> (@saladstopsg) on <time style=\" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;\" datetime=\"2018-09-28T00:00:55+00:00\">Sep 27, 2018 at 5:00pm PDT</time></p></div></blockquote><script async src=\"//www.instagram.com/embed.js\"></script>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>‚ÄúWhat makes me the happiest and the most motivated is when I see our team behind the cashier or salad bar being passionate about our movement or educating customers on going vegan or not using plastic.‚Äù <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Tips for businesses in becoming more sustainable</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Two words: be focused. ‚ÄúLook at the area where you can impact the most.<br>If it‚Äôs in the takeaway packaging, focus on that and make a change and move on to the next area of focus. Don‚Äôt try to do it all at once. Let‚Äôs educate customers along the way, comfort the world and show them an authentic reality of a business, one that is incredibly transparent.‚Äù</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ending with her favourite quote by Robert Swan, ‚ÄúThe greatest threat to our planet is the belief that someone else will save it.‚Äù<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>‚ÄúIf more people realised that it is in the power of the individual ‚Äî and only the individual ‚Äî then things would move a lot faster.‚Äù</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>If you want your business and/or favourite businesses to be a part of PACT, find out more </em><a href=\"http://www.wwf.sg/pact.cfm\"><em>here</em></a><em>. </em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>This article is most updated on July 24, 2019.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Read also: </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/plastics-in-nature/2019/01/plastic-straw-business-owner-pact-wwf/\"><strong><em>five questions to ask yourself if you are a business owner</em></strong></a><strong><em>, </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/sustainable-consumption/2019/01/marie-kondo-declutter-our-planet-wwf/\"><strong><em>reasons why our planet needs Marie Kondo</em></strong></a><strong><em> and </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/ocean/2018/11/plastic-pollution-opinion-businesses-pact/\"><strong><em>why plastic is not the villain</em></strong></a><strong><em>.</em></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p> </p>\n","uri":"salad-stop-katherine-braha-sustainable-no-plastic/","author":{"name":"Sharon Salim","slug":"ssalim","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e36b8ae309f36dfc7c9fe446f89fd97d?s=96&d=mm&r=g"}},"featuredImage":{"altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/OUR-2018-ROUND-UP-10.jpg 1000w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/OUR-2018-ROUND-UP-10-300x225.jpg 300w"},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"katherine braha","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/katherine-braha/","slug":"katherine-braha"},{"name":"no plastics in nature","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/no-plastics-in-nature/","slug":"no-plastics-in-nature"},{"name":"PACT","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/pact/","slug":"pact"},{"name":"plastics free","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/plastics-free/","slug":"plastics-free"},{"name":"saladstop!","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/saladstop/","slug":"saladstop"},{"name":"single-use plastics","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/single-use-plastics/","slug":"single-use-plastics"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Personality feature","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/personality-feature/","slug":"personality-feature"},{"name":"Plastics in Nature","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/plastics-in-nature/","slug":"plastics-in-nature"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"cG9zdDo0MDI5","uri":"salad-stop-katherine-braha-sustainable-no-plastic/","title":"Salad Stop!‚Äôs Katherine Braha on Building a Sustainable Business","databaseId":4029,"slug":"salad-stop-katherine-braha-sustainable-no-plastic","excerpt":"<p>Co-founder and director of Salad Stop! Katherine Braha is not only passionate about everything marketing-related, but the mother-of-one is also pushing the brand to go plastic-free. SaladStop! has joined PACT, a voluntary business-led Plastic ACTion commitment on plastic. Since the start of 2019, the sustainable food business has implemented a plastic and paper bag charge [&hellip;]</p>\n","date":"2019-01-30T18:14:56"}}}